### REST Client Requests for Rateio API
### Use the REST Client extension (humao.rest-client) in VS Code
### Click "Send Request" above each request to execute it

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@apiUrl = {{baseUrl}}/api

### Variables (update these with your actual values)
@chargeId = ch_xxxxx
@transactionId = tran_A17rDE1ubDUBdR0Q
@rateioId = c8de05ad-e01e-4205-ab9c-589aa0f647c8
@participantId = 3e5c99d4-db98-4376-a3ca-def199ab21b5

###############################################
# WEBHOOK TEST ENDPOINTS
###############################################

### Find Charge ID from Participant ID
GET {{apiUrl}}/webhook/pagarme/find-charge/{{participantId}}

### Simulate Payment - Using Charge ID
POST {{apiUrl}}/webhook/pagarme/test
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "chargeId": "{{chargeId}}",
  "amount": 300,
  "type": "charge.paid"
}

### Simulate Payment - Using Participant ID (Easiest!)
POST {{apiUrl}}/webhook/pagarme/test
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "participantId": "{{participantId}}",
  "amount": 300,
  "type": "charge.paid"
}

### Simulate Payment - Using Transaction ID
POST {{apiUrl}}/webhook/pagarme/test
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "transactionId": "{{transactionId}}",
  "amount": 300,
  "type": "charge.paid"
}

### Simulate Payment - Using Transaction ID (Example)
POST {{apiUrl}}/webhook/pagarme/test
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "transactionId": "tran_923EpaaFxBHzLOxp",
  "amount": 300,
  "type": "charge.paid"
}

### Simulate Refund
POST {{apiUrl}}/webhook/pagarme/test
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "chargeId": "{{chargeId}}",
  "amount": 300,
  "type": "charge.refunded"
}

### Simulate Failed Payment
POST {{apiUrl}}/webhook/pagarme/test
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "chargeId": "{{chargeId}}",
  "amount": 300,
  "type": "charge.failed"
}

###############################################
# RATEIO ENDPOINTS (tRPC)
###############################################

### Get Rateio by ID
POST {{baseUrl}}/trpc/rateio.getById
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "json": {
    "id": "{{rateioId}}"
  }
}

### Get Rateios by Creator
POST {{baseUrl}}/trpc/rateio.getByCreator
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "json": {}
}

### Get Participants by Rateio
POST {{baseUrl}}/trpc/participant.getByRateio
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "json": {
    "rateioId": "{{rateioId}}"
  }
}

### Get Participant by ID
POST {{baseUrl}}/trpc/participant.getById
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "json": {
    "id": "{{participantId}}"
  }
}

### Create Payment Intent
POST {{baseUrl}}/trpc/payment.createIntent
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "json": {
    "participantId": "{{participantId}}",
    "amount": 300
  }
}

### Get Payment Status
POST {{baseUrl}}/trpc/payment.getStatus
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "json": {
    "participantId": "{{participantId}}"
  }
}

###############################################
# PAGAR.ME API ENDPOINTS (Direct)
###############################################

### Get Charge Status (requires Pagar.me credentials)
GET https://api.pagar.me/core/v5/charges/{{chargeId}}
Authorization: Basic {{$dotenv PAGARME_API_KEY}}
Content-Type: application/json

### List Recent Charges
GET https://api.pagar.me/core/v5/charges?size=50&page=1
Authorization: Basic {{$dotenv PAGARME_API_KEY}}
Content-Type: application/json

###############################################
# NOTES
###############################################

### How to use:
### 1. Install REST Client extension in VS Code
### 2. Update variables at the top with your actual values
### 3. Click "Send Request" above any request to execute it
### 
### For Pagar.me endpoints, set PAGARME_API_KEY in your .env file
### Format: PAGARME_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
###
### The webhook test endpoint bypasses signature validation
### and allows simulating payments for testing purposes.

